Interface Fn0<V>

  • Type Parameters:
    V - Type of value yielded from the function.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    LazyVal<V>

    public interface Fn0<V>
    A function which provides a value, without taking any arguments. It can be used to lazily calculate a value, or yield its result based on closing over some local or global value(s).
